TY  - JOUR
AU  - Scherbina, Anna
AU  - Schlusche, Bernd
T1  - Follow the Leader: Using the Stock Market to Uncover Information Flows between Firms*
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfy038
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
SP  - 189
EP  - 225
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We identify all return leader–follower pairs among individual stocks using Granger causality regressions. Thus-identified leaders reliably predict their followers’ returns out of sample, and the return predictability works at the level of individual stocks rather than industries. Our results indicate that, independent of its size, any firm may emerge as a return leader by being at the center of an important news development that has ramifications for other firms. Indeed, stocks undergoing news-generating developments see an increase in the number of stocks whose returns they lead.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfy038
ER  - 



