TY  - JOUR
AU  - De Jonghe, Olivier
AU  - Dewachter, Hans
AU  - Mulier, Klaas
AU  - Ongena, Steven
AU  - Schepens, Glenn
T1  - Some Borrowers Are More Equal than Others: Bank Funding Shocks and Credit Reallocation*
PY  - 2020
Y1  - 2020/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfy040
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 43
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - This paper provides evidence on the strategic lending decisions made by banks facing a negative funding shock. Using bank–firm level credit data, we show that banks reallocate credit within their loan portfolio in at least three different ways. First, banks reallocate to sectors where they have a high market share. Second, they also reallocate to sectors in which they are more specialized. Third, they reallocate credit toward low-risk firms. These reallocation effects are economically large. A standard deviation increase in sector market share, sector specialization, or firm soundness reduces the transmission of the funding shock to credit supply by 22%, 8%, and 10%, respectively.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfy040
ER  - 



